:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-5ut","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":40000,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/05\/11\/overstay-welcome\/","url_meta":{"origin":21109,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Guests: Warning not to overstay your welcome","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Shurayh reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cHospitality for the guest is no more than three days, and it is courteous to host for one day and night. It is not lawful for a Muslim man to reside with his brother until he tempts him\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28159,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/26\/witr-beginning-middle-end\/","url_meta":{"origin":21109,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Witr: The Prophet prays Witr before dawn","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 26, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would perform Witr prayer every night, either at the beginning, middle, or end of the night, finishing his Witr prayer before the break of dawn. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 996, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 745 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32976,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/forgives-between-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":21109,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Allah forgives what one did between prayers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cA Muslim man does not perform ablution in an excellent manner and then performs prayer, but that Allah will forgive him for what occurred between his prayer and the next.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 158, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7501,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/03\/curse-own-parents\/","url_meta":{"origin":21109,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Curses: Prohibition of cursing another&#8217;s parents","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, among the major sins is that a man curses his own parents.\u201d It was said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, how can a man curse his own parents?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cHe insults the father\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":761,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/05\/07\/never-say-allah-not-forgive\/","url_meta":{"origin":21109,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Arrogance: Never say Allah will not forgive someone","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 7, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Jundab reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said,\u00a0\u201cA man said: By Allah, Allah will not forgive this person! Allah Almighty said: Who is he who swore by Me that I will not forgive someone? I have forgiven him and erased your good deeds.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7655,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/05\/cursing-killing-muslim-kufr\/","url_meta":{"origin":21109,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Muslims: Cursing him is wicked, killing is unbelief","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas'ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDisparaging a Muslim is an act of wickedness, and fighting him is an act of unbelief.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 7076, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 64 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/21109","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuami